Virgil has broken off his conversation with Statius in order
to address Dante (with an Italian version of the Latin vocative case:
'figliuole,' verse 4).  As Singleton (comm. to verse 5) points out, all
three of the similar warnings on the part of the protagonist's guide
that the journey must be completed within a definite period occur in
the 'next-to-last circle of each of the three realms' (see also ^Inf~.
XXIX.10-12; ^Par~. XXII.124 [the eighth of the nine heavenly spheres]).
